{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id5a5788a0-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s631"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"631"},"text":"§ 631.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Age limits","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id5a5788a1-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s631/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Individuals at least 40 years of age","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The prohibitions in this chapter shall be limited to individuals who are at least 40 years of age.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id5a5788a2-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s631/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Employees or applicants for employment in Federal Government","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of any personnel action affecting employees or applicants for employment which is subject to the provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s633a"},"text":"section 633a of this title","children":[],"tail":", the prohibitions established in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s633a"},"text":"section 633a of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall be limited to individuals who are at least 40 years of age."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id5a5788a3-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s631/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Bona fide executives or high policymakers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id5a5788a4-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s631/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to prohibit compulsory retirement of any employee who has attained 65 years of age and who, for the 2-year period immediately before retirement, is employed in a bona fide executive or a high policymaking position, if such employee is entitled to an immediate nonforfeitable annual retirement benefit from a pension, profit-sharing, savings, or deferred compensation plan, or any combination of such plans, of the employer of such employee, which equals, in the aggregate, at least $44,000.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id5a5788a5-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s631/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In applying the retirement benefit test of paragraph (1) of this subsection, if any such retirement benefit is in a form other than a straight life annuity (with no ancillary benefits), or if employees contribute to any such plan or make rollover contributions, such benefit shall be adjusted in accordance with regulations prescribed by the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission, after consultation with the Secretary of the Treasury, so that the benefit is the equivalent of a straight life annuity (with no ancillary benefits) under a plan to which employees do not contribute and under which no rollover contributions are made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id5a5788a6-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/202/s12"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–202, § 12","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-12-15"},"text":"Dec. 15, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/607"},"text":"81 Stat. 607","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/256/s3/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–256, § 3(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b)(3), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-04-06"},"text":"Apr. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/189"},"text":"92 Stat. 189","children":[],"tail":", 190; 1978 Reorg. Plan No. 1, § 2, eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", 43 F.R. 19807, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/3781"},"text":"92 Stat. 3781","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/459/tVIII/s802/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–459, title VIII, § 802(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-09"},"text":"Oct. 9, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1792"},"text":"98 Stat. 1792","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/272/tIX/s9201/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–272, title IX, § 9201(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-04-07"},"text":"Apr. 7, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/171"},"text":"100 Stat. 171","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/592"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–592","children":[],"tail":", §§ 2(c), 6(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-31"},"text":"Oct. 31, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3342"},"text":"100 Stat. 3342","children":[],"tail":", 3344; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239/tVI/s6202/b/3/C/ii"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239, title VI, § 6202(b)(3)(C)(ii)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/2233"},"text":"103 Stat. 2233","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id5a59f9a7-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id5a59f9a8-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id5a59f9a9-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239","children":[],"tail":" struck out “(except the provisions of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s623/g"},"text":"section 623(g) of this title","children":[],"tail":")” after “in this chapter”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/592/s2/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–592, § 2(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", which directed that “but less than seventy years of age” be struck out was executed by striking out “but less than 70 years of age” after “40 years of age” as the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/272"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–272","children":[],"tail":" inserted “(except the provisions of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s623/g"},"text":"section 623(g) of this title","children":[],"tail":")” after “this chapter”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/592/s2/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–592, § 2(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", which directed that “but not seventy years of age,” be struck out was executed by striking out “but not 70 years of age,” after “65 years of age” as the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/592/s6/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–592, § 6(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), temporarily added subsec. (d) which read as follows: “Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to prohibit compulsory retirement of any employee who has attained 70 years of age, and who is serving under a contract of unlimited tenure (or similar arrangement providing for unlimited tenure) at an institution of higher education (as defined by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s1141/a"},"text":"section 1141(a) of title 20","children":[],"tail":").” See Effective and Termination Dates of 1986 Amendments note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/459"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–459","children":[],"tail":" substituted “$44,000” for “$27,000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/256/s3/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–256, § 3(a)","children":[],"tail":", designated existing provisions as subsec. (a), substituted “40 years of age but less than 70 years of age” for “forty years of age but less than sixty-five years of age”, added subsecs. (b) and (c), and temporarily added subsec. (d). See Effective and Termination Dates of 1978 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id5a59f9aa-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment